The paper deals with image retrieval and hashing techniques, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of deep neural networks for feature extraction and adversarial learning also suggests a connection to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the application of the proposed method to fashion inventory search may also relate to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
